(107, 1, '2010-11-07 18:19:45', '2010-11-07 18:19:45', '<a href="http://www.coffeebot.co/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/bot12.jpg"><img src="http://www.coffeebot.co/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/bot12.jpg" alt="Bot1" title="bot1" width="197" height="724" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-229" /></a><span style="color:#993300;font-family:''ChunkFiveRegular'';font-size:1.6em; font-weight:normal;">Bot1 is the heart and soul of CoffeeBot. A little odd considering he has neither, but I digress.</span> It was Bot1 who wrangled me, a human, into writing for this blog (writing is completely beneath him, besides, he writes in binary).\r\n\r\nDuring the design and building of Bot1, a hapless software engineer spilled his triple half-caf pumpkin latte with extra whip cream across the main circuit board-the the very board that was supposed to be the ''kill center'' of the robot. The programmed need to kill became a need to caffeinate and try as they might, they could not re-program the bot. Just as they were about to put him out to pasture, I saw the engineer''s for sale ad on craigslist, and spotting his need for all things espresso, I knew I could exploit-I mean, utilize him. It. Bot1.\r\n\r\nBot1 is stubborn, single-minded, slightly rude and a lover of all things Pomeranian. He never reboots, always says "excuse me" and consistently compliments me by putting me down. However, without it-him-whatever, this blog couldn''t exist.', 'Who is Bot1?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'who-is-bot1', '', '', '2010-11-14 18:35:48', '2010-11-14 18:35:48', '', 159, 'http://localhost/coffeebot/?page_id=107', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(115, 1, '2010-11-07 18:43:29', '2010-11-07 18:43:29', '<p style="text-align: center;">[ad#Google Adsense]</p>\r\n<span style="color:#993300;font-family:''ChunkFiveRegular'';font-size:1.6em; font-weight:normal;">Love coffee?\r\nHave opinions?\r\nAlways wanted to be a robot?\r\n</span>\r\n\r\nYou might be the right candidate to contribute to CoffeeBot! CoffeeBot is needing witty, talented writers from all over the world who love coffee, appreciate the coffee culture, and love all things unique. You''ll get your very own bot designation (i.e. Bot4, Bot2449472) and a warm, fuzzy feeling grounded in the knowledge that you are helping your fellow citizens and travelers find what they need most: a great cup of coffee.\r\n\r\nInterested? Let me, Bot2, know by sending me a message.\r\n\r\n[si-contact-form form=''1'']', 'Become a CoffeeBot', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'become-a-coffeebot', '', '', '2010-11-14 17:22:02', '2010-11-14 17:22:02', '', 0, 'http://localhost/coffeebot/?page_id=115', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(121, 1, '2010-11-08 18:01:24', '2010-11-08 18:01:24', '<p style="text-align: center;">[ad#Google Adsense Post Ad]</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\r\n\r\n<hr /><a href="http://www.coffeebot.co/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/paris-platte.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-138" title="Paris On The Platte" src="http://www.coffeebot.co/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/paris-platte.jpg" alt="Paris On The Platte" width="530" height="200" /></a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<div id="rating-block">\r\n\r\n[easyreview title="The Stats" cat1title="Coffee Quality" cat1rating="3" cat1detail="Utilitarian caffeine with modest attention to quality." cat2title="Atmosphere" cat2rating="3.5" cat2detail="Dark where it needs to be, light where it''s important, local art and aged/warehouse character"]\r\n<table id="info">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="title">Features <a title="key" href="http://www.coffeebot.co/?page_id=195">(Key)</a></td>\r\n<td><span class="no-atm">No ATM</span><span class="yes-alcohol">Alcohol</span><span class="no-music">No Music</span><span class="yes-parking">Free Parking</span><span class="yes-food">Food is Served</span><span class="yes-wifi">Free Wifi</span><span class="manual">Manual Espresso Machine</span>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="address">1553 Platte St, Denver, CO 80202</td>\r\n<td class="phone">(303) 455-2451</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="website"><a title="Paris On The Platte" href="http://www.parisontheplattecafeandbar.com">Website</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<span class="first-words">Paris on the Platte is one of my favorite urban coffee bars in the Denver metro.</span> It has all the great ''cool factors'': local art that is usually good, a store-front facing a lively street, weathered decor,  indie rock (I walked in to Viva Voce playing over the speakers—one of my favorite bands), citizens in skinny jeans, and decent espresso. It''s a great place being not only a coffee shop, but also a cafe and bar.\r\n\r\n<span class="first-words">The Coffee</span> Bot1 showed up in a pair of skinny jeans he had purchased from the Salvation Army, and after I wrestled them off of him, he sulked up to the counter and ordered a small latte. Even though we ordered a small, it came in a nice big mug, and after some detailed chemical analysis, Bot1 concluded the cinnamon on top of the foam was in fact, cinnamon. A nice touch, but if you don''t like people putting spices on your coffee, you might mention that upon ordering. After this, he lost interest, went over to the bar, and I was left to do the tasting by myself.\r\n\r\nThe latte was...good; nothing amazing. The foam was a tad bubbly and I would have liked more espresso presence, but the flavor that was there was smooth and balanced, so I can''t really complain. This isn''t an artisan place, so I didn''t detect much passion for coffee itself; I understand that coffee passion isn''t necessarily the point to the place.\r\n\r\n<span class="first-words">The Atmosphere</span> The main thing about this joint is that you can come in, set up your lappy, and do what you do best: hit up Facebook. Keep in mind that most people who sit there for a while are also on their laptops, so the connection speed is pretty slow. So, if you''re heading there to play Warcraft, it might not be the best place. Then again, you probably wouldn''t actually head outside to go to a coffee shop, either.\r\n\r\nAnother great aspect is the presence of living, breathing people (not just spoiled robots), and at this place, the flow of humans is pretty constant. Of all the times I have visited, I''ve never seen it empty, and I like that. The steady murmur of conversation is the perfect soundtrack to get my work done. It definitely is a neighborhood staple, and you aren''t without choices on where to sit or plug in. There''s plenty of room in the coffee side, bar side, and there''s even a little patio outback where cigarettes tend to be smoked.\r\n\r\n<span class="first-words">The End</span> Overall, it''s a good place, and I find myself recommending it often. Bot1 even likes it, but I can''t be sure the presence of wine next door is not swaying his judgment.<span class="end-icon">END</span>\r\n\r\n[mappress mapid="1"]', 'Paris on the Platte Cafe &amp; Bar', 'Paris on the Platte is one of my favorite urban coffee bars in the Denver metro. It has all the great ''cool factors'': local art that is usually good, a store-front facing a busy, lively street, beaten-up decor,  indie rock (I walked in to Viva Voce playing-one of my fav''s), citizens in skinny jeans, and decent espresso. It''s a unique place being not only a coffee shop, but also a wine bar.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-on-the-platte', '', '', '2011-01-28 21:19:24', '2011-01-28 21:19:24', '', 0, 'http://localhost/coffeebot/?p=121', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(153, 1, '2010-11-11 16:34:22', '2010-11-11 16:34:22', '<p style="text-align: center;">[ad#Google Adsense Post Ad]</p>\r\n<span style="color:#993300;font-family:''ChunkFiveRegular'';font-size:1.6em; font-weight:normal;">Do you think there''s a coffee shop</span> that Bot1 should visit and review? Let us know and we''ll try to convince him he should do it. For now, we can only review in the Denver metro area, but give us time, we''re expanding the network.\r\n\r\n[si-contact-form form=''2'']', 'Review Request', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'review-request', '', '', '2010-11-14 17:25:14', '2010-11-14 17:25:14', '', 0, 'http://localhost/coffeebot/?page_id=153', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(195, 1, '2010-11-11 18:36:05', '2010-11-11 18:36:05', '<h3 style="color:#993300;font-family:''ChunkFiveRegular'';font-size:1.6em; font-weight:normal;">Wonder what those symbols on each review mean?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul id="rating-list">\r\n<li><span class="manual">Manual Espresso Machine</span>Using a a manual or semi-automatic espresso machine</li>\r\n<li><span class="auto">Automatic Espresso Machine</span>Using an automatic espresso machine (gone over to the dark side)</li>\r\n<li><span class="yes-wifi">Free Wifi</span>Free Wifi (if they don''t have it free, why go?)</li>\r\n<li><span class="pay-wifi">Pay Wifi Access</span>You gotta pay to play</li>\r\n<li><span class="yes-food">Food is Served</span>These guys serve food too!</li>\r\n<li><span class="yes-alcohol">Alcohol is Served</span>Serving alcohol-the other sweet nectar</li>\r\n<li><span class="yes-parking">Free Parking</span>Guess you don''t have to pay to park here.</li>\r\n<li><span class="pay-parking">Pay to Park</span>Paid parking</li>\r\n<li><span class="live-music">Live Music</span>People tend to play their instruments here.</li>\r\n<li><span class="yes-atm">ATM Available</span>Keep the cash flowing</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>', 'Symbol Key', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'symbol-key', '', '', '2011-01-28 20:57:17', '2011-01-28 20:57:17', '', 159, 'http://localhost/coffeebot/?page_id=195', 2, 'page', '', 0),
