(240, 1, '2010-09-05 16:09:52', '2010-09-05 16:09:52', '<p style="text-align: center;">[ad#Google Adsense]</p>\n<hr />\n<a href="http://localhost/coffeebot/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/forza.jpg"><img src="http://localhost/coffeebot/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/forza.jpg" alt="Forza Coffee" title="forza" width="528" height="200" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-280" /></a>\n<hr />\n<div id="rating-block">\n\n[easyreview title="The Stats" cat1title="Coffee Quality" cat1rating="3.5" cat1detail="The employees seem to care & their product, and the result is a decent product." cat2title="Atmosphere" cat2rating="3.5" cat2detail="Lot''s of seating, fireplace, power outlets, local art, competent interior design."]\n\n<table id="info">\n  <tr>\n    <td class="title">Features <a href="http://localhost/coffeebot/?page_id=195" title="key">(Key)</a></td>\n    <td><span class="food">Food</span><span class="free-parking">Free parking</span><span class="wifi">WiFi</span><span class="manual">WiFi</span></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n     <td class="address">3013 W. 104th Ave. Ste. 700, Westminster, CO 80031</td>\n     <td class="phone">(303) 465-0605</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n     <td class="website"><a href="http://www.rmforzacoffee.com" title="Forza Coffee">Website</a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n</div>\n\n<span class="first-words">I was trying to decide which coffee house to review first for CoffeeBot.</span>  Not the most easy decision to make considering here in the Denver metro area we have close to 10 x 8 to the third carry the two coffee shops. OK, not that many, but still. Luckily, Bot1 made the decision for me, and it''s a good one: Forza Coffee in Westminster. I know, I know, a suburban coffee shop, but bear with me...<!--more-->\n\n<h4><span class="first-words">The History</span></h4> From what I know about this place, its pedigree is traced back to Tacoma, Washington—not a bad place to come from, I suppose. Their self-description talks of being a vital part of the community and being inspired by Italy''s espresso culture, yada yada yada. Nearly everyone says that. Even Howard Schultz said that at one time and look where that got us. However, their expressed desire to be a neighborhood coffee shop seems to actually be working.\n\n<h4><span class="first-words">The Coffee</span></h4> My standard first-time drink is usually an Americano or latte. In this case, the Americano is a wonderful baseline drink. If made correctly, you get a lovely crema, the hot water and espresso combination even out the flavor of the coffee, and let''s face it: espresso is gone way too fast. I''m not Italian, for Pete''s sake. I love espresso shots but will only drink it straight in places I really trust. To my delight, I heard the familiar banging of portafilters into bins, and I had a feeling I was in for a treat. The drink was produced and brought to my table, whereupon I viewed that  nice layer of crema. The flavor was good. Not amazing, but good. The espresso certainly embodied everything a fine espresso should: full body, slight bitterness, subtle caramel tones; but for me, the dimension didn''t go far enough. That''s hardly a negative, since the intensity of espresso is, after all, subjective.\n\n<h4><span class="first-words">The Atmosphere</span></h4> For once, this is a suburban coffee shop that is actually comfortable and has a hint of urban dinge that in my opinion, all the best coffee shops have. Sometimes, the dingier the better. The deep yellow-gold, black, copper and dark wood mix well to form a comfortable and inspiring atmosphere. Armed with a great comfy-couch area and plenty of tables (including outside seating) you definitely have your choice of places to sit. Mine, however, was by the fireplace. And that''s enough about the design, I drink coffee, after all.\n\n<h4><span class="first-words">The End</span></h4> Finally, the experience was punctuated by genuinely nice staff. I''ve been a few times, and even Bot1 has sneaked over there a couple times when I haven''t been looking. Witty small talk and a staff that calls  you by name on the second visit is a good step in the direction of having a lasting neighborhood coffee shop.<span class="end-icon">END</span>\n[mappress]', 'Forza Coffee', 'I was trying to decide which coffee house to review first for Coffee-Bot. Not the most easy decision to make considering here in the Denver metro area we have close to 10 x 8 to the third carry the two...coffee shops. OK, not that many, but still. Luckily, Bot1 made the decision for me, and it''s a good one: Forza Coffee in Westminster. I know, I know, a suburban coffee shop, but bear with me...', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '160-revision', '', '', '2010-09-05 16:09:52', '2010-09-05 16:09:52', '', 160, 'http://coffeebot.co/?p=240', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(241, 1, '2010-11-07 18:43:29', '2010-11-07 18:43:29', '<p style="text-align: center;">[ad#Google Adsense]</p>\n<span style="color:#993300;font-family:''ChunkFiveRegular'';font-size:1.6em; font-weight:normal;">Love coffee?\nHave opinions?\nAlways wanted to be a robot?\n</span>\n\nYou might be the right candidate to contribute to CoffeeBot! CoffeeBot is needing witty, talented writers from all over the world who love coffee, appreciate the coffee culture, and love all things unique. You''ll get your very own bot designation (i.e. Bot4, Bot2449472) and a warm, fuzzy feeling grounded in the knowledge that you are helping your fellow citizens and travelers find what they need most: a great cup of coffee.\n\nInterested? Let me, Bot2, know by sending me a message.\n\n[si-contact-form form=''1'']', 'Become a CoffeeBot', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '115-revision', '', '', '2010-11-07 18:43:29', '2010-11-07 18:43:29', '', 115, 'http://coffeebot.co/?p=241', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(242, 1, '2010-11-11 16:34:22', '2010-11-11 16:34:22', '<p style="text-align: center;">[ad#Google Adsense]</p>\n<span style="color:#993300;font-family:''ChunkFiveRegular'';font-size:1.6em; font-weight:normal;">Do you think there''s a coffee shop</span> that Bot1 should visit and review? Let us know and we''ll try to convince him he should do it. For now, we can only review in the Denver metro area, but give us time, we''re expanding the network.\n\n[si-contact-form form=''2'']', 'Review Request', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '153-revision', '', '', '2010-11-11 16:34:22', '2010-11-11 16:34:22', '', 153, 'http://coffeebot.co/?p=242', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
