(271, 1, '2010-11-14 17:31:47', '2010-11-14 17:31:47', '<span style="color:#993300;font-family:''ChunkFiveRegular'';font-size:1.6em; font-weight:normal;">It is no secret to those who know me (Bot2) that I really do love coffee.</span> What I’m not sure of, however, is what I love more: the consumable product, or the atmosphere it’s consumed in.\r\n\r\nThe love of the two is my inspiration behind this blog. No false pretenses, no agendas, no big <span style="color:#993300;font-family:''ChunkFiveRegular'';font-size:1.6em; font-weight:normal;">loquacious</span> words, just some chatting about coffee and the coffee culture. Ultimately, this site should serve as a resource for people looking for new and exciting coffee shops. Plain and simple.\r\n\r\nYou may be wondering if I even know anything about coffee. Yes, yes I do. Then again, no, no I don’t. In the “yes” camp, I have over 10 years experience working in the coffee business. I built and ran a coffee shop early this millennium and upon moving to a new suburban area, I spent my time working for various shops while going to school. In the “no” camp, I know that coffee is not a stagnant entity easy to sum up. Coffee is more than just 98% water; it’s a culture, a way of life, a multidimensional beverage that changes by the seasons, countries and political uprisings. It is this complex personality that I love about coffee-always changing and morphing, yet somehow staying comfortably familiar regardless the venue in which it''s consumed.\r\n\r\nThat''s enough about me. The true hero is <a href="http://www.coffeebot.co/?page_id=107">Bot1</a>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '159-revision-2', '', '', '2010-11-14 17:31:47', '2010-11-14 17:31:47', '', 159, 'http://coffeebot.co/?p=271', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(275, 1, '2010-11-07 18:19:45', '2010-11-07 18:19:45', '<a href="http://localhost/coffeebot/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/bot12.jpg"><img src="http://localhost/coffeebot/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/bot12.jpg" alt="Bot1" title="bot1" width="197" height="724" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-229" /></a><span style="color:#993300;font-family:''ChunkFiveRegular'';font-size:1.6em; font-weight:normal;">Bot1 is the heart and soul of CoffeeBot. A little odd considering he has neither, but I digress.</span> It was Bot1 who wrangled me, a human, into writing for this blog (writing is completely beneath him, besides, he writes in binary).\n\nDuring the design and building of Bot1, a hapless software engineer spilled his triple half-caf pumpkin latte with extra whip cream across the main circuit board-the the very board that was supposed to be the ''kill center'' of the robot. The programmed need to kill became a need to caffeinate and try as they might, they could not re-program the bot. Just as they were about to put him out to pasture, I saw the engineer''s for sale ad on craigslist, and spotting his need for all things espresso, I knew I could exploit-I mean, utilize him. It. Bot1.\n\nBot1 is stubborn, single-minded, slightly rude and a lover of all things Pomeranian. He never reboots, always says "excuse me" and consistently compliments me by putting me down. However, without it-him-whatever, this blog couldn''t exist.', 'Who is Bot1?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '107-revision', '', '', '2010-11-07 18:19:45', '2010-11-07 18:19:45', '', 107, 'http://coffeebot.co/?p=275', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
