(380, 1, '2010-12-20 20:23:27', '2010-12-20 20:23:27', '<script src="http://connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js#xfbml=1"></script><fb:like show_faces="true" width="528”></fb:like>\r\n<div id="rating-block">\r\n\r\n<a href="http://coffeebot.co/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/illegal-grounds.jpg"><img src="http://coffeebot.co/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/illegal-grounds.jpg" alt="Illegal Grounds Coffee Shop" title="illegal-grounds" width="528" height="200" class="size-full wp-image-365" /></a>\r\n\r\n<div id="rating-block">\r\n[easyreview title="The Stats" cat1title="Coffee Quality" cat1rating="2.5" cat1detail="Utilitarian coffee: drinkable but nothing special." cat2title="Atmosphere" cat2rating="3" cat2detail="Cozy living room feel but with a good amount of seating."]\r\n<table id="info">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="title">Features <a href="http://localhost/coffeebot/?page_id=195" title="key">(Key)</a></td>\r\n<td><span class="wifi">WiFi</span><span class="auto">Automatic Machine</span><span class="food">Pastries</span><span class="free-parking">Free street parking</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="address">925 East 17th Avenue, Denver, CO 80202</td>\r\n<td class="phone">(720) 434-0434</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="website">No website</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<span class="first-words">Bot1 insisted on Illegal Grounds in Denver''s Uptown neighborhood this time around.</span> He insisted because he is convinced anything with the word “Illegal” in it has to be awesome. If you remember back to his reading of “Death Beam” a few posts ago, you know that I try to discourage anything that might be violent or illegal...or involve the word “death”. He may be a caffeine-converted bot, but there is no escaping what he was originally built for. However, I digress.\r\n\r\nIllegal Grounds, despite its name which implies a certain badness coupled with scary tattoos (or maybe the fact it was started by a lawyer?), is a very tame and inviting neighborhood coffee shop. Situated on the ground floor of an old Victorian house,  it embodies all the charms of a local favorite. Upon entrance, you walk straight in down a hallway to the counter, and in my case, was met by a very friendly employee.\r\n\r\n<span class="first-words">The Coffee.</span> An Americano was ordered and with it in hand, I turned the corner, entered the living room, and flopped down on one of the couches. Ultimately, I wasn''t going to expect much from the cup of coffee. The machine was automatic and they serve Illy coffee. Whenever I experience this kind of scenario, this usually translates to a very tame, albeit drinkable, cup of coffee. And I was right. There were no overwhelming flavors or distinctions to the espresso, just utilitarian goodness. I know, I sound snooty when I immediately dismiss a beverage produced from an automatic machine, especially since this blog is called Coffee Bot which implies a certain level of automation, but understand that ultimately it is the human element in the creation of a beverage that gives it its ultimate dimension and uniqueness. It''s that which fuels my passion for exceptional coffee.\r\n\r\n<span class="first-words">The Atmosphere.</span> The atmosphere didn''t disappoint. Once I rounded the corner into the seating area (or living room), I was immediately impressed with how many tables and chairs were fit amid the cozy space. A large picture window at the end of the room gave a bright, framed view of 17th street, and the light that poured in lit the walls full of local art. Wood floors, quiet music and a plentiful supply of power strips made Illegal Grounds a perfect spot to hunker down and get straight to conversation, work, or relaxation.  \r\n\r\n<span class="first-words">The End.</span> Even though Bot1 didn''t fit easily between the tables and chairs, I would say our visit was a success and we will definitely return. The coffee gets the job done, the employees were very friendly,  and the atmosphere makes you want to hang around a little longer than you might at another coffee shop. \r\n[mappress mapid="8"]\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">[ad#Google Adsense Post Ad]</p>\r\n<hr />', 'Illegal Grounds ', 'Illegal Grounds, despite its name which implies a certain badness coupled with scary tattoos (or maybe the fact it was started by a lawyer?), is a very tame and inviting neighborhood coffee shop. Situated on the ground floor of an old Victorian house,  it embodies all the charms of a local favorite. Upon entrance, you walk straight in down a hallway to the counter, and in my case, was met by a very friendly employee.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '364-revision-15', '', '', '2010-12-20 20:23:27', '2010-12-20 20:23:27', '', 364, 'http://coffeebot.co/uncategorized/364-revision-15/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
