(317, 1, '2010-12-05 19:30:41', '2010-12-05 19:30:41', 'Bot1 had just completed a lecture at CU on the intricacies of wiring a common household goldfish, and like he is after every lecture, found his system needing a certain caffeine boost. We found ourselves at Folsom St. Coffee Co. This is a college joint through and through, and the day we visited it was its usual self: packed, hip...and green. According to their website, Folsom St. Coffee is “Boulder''s only true eco-friendly coffeehouse. Folsom St. Coffee Co. was awarded the Eco-Cycle award for ''Zero Waste or Darn Near'' as well as the "Waste Reduction" award from the Center For Resource Conservation.” I believe it, because when Bot1 tried to throw away his trash, his waste eliminating algorithm caused his CPU to overheat just trying to sort out which tub to throw what in. \n\nBack to the coffee. As has become customary, a double espresso was ordered and Bot1 left to talk up a couple students who were sitting outside. The espresso presented to me had a deceivingly beautiful thick crema that held fast when I spooned some sugar on top. That was a good sign. The flavor, however, was a disappointment. Oddly enough I felt like I was drinking a lime. Of course there were most of the typical espresso qualities, but the acidity was shocking! I''d like to attribute this to the extraction of the shot, but I watched it pour and everything was on the up and up. The flavor evened out when it was in an Americano, but overall I wasn''t too impressed with the flavor.\n\nLike many coffee shops, however, the experience doesn''t always center around the coffee, and ultimately Folsom St. Coffee delivered in other areas. The atmosphere was welcoming, cozy and was the sort of place in which I felt I could get motivated to finally write my 20 page single-spaced essay on the relationship between Pyongyang and Beijing. The muddled and haphazard decor actually cemented the cozy feeling, and that constant murmur of a packed coffee house was ideal for working, meeting friends, or simply sipping a cup of coffee. Complete with poetry, open mic nights and live music acts, this place is hopping a good part of every day, and the sort of place young hipsters like to frequent. \n\nOverall this coffee shop is very enjoyable, and despite being turned down three whole times, Bot1 vowed it wouldn''t keep him down and will definitely return. While the coffee didn''t bowl me over, if you keep it to lattes, Americanos, and brews you won''t be disappointed.  ', 'Folsom St. Coffee Company', 'Bot1 had just completed a lecture at CU on the intricacies of wiring a common household goldfish, and like he is after every lecture, found his system needing a certain caffeine boost. We found ourselves at Folsom St. Coffee Co. ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '316-revision', '', '', '2010-12-05 19:30:41', '2010-12-05 19:30:41', '', 316, 'http://coffeebot.co/?p=317', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(318, 1, '2010-12-06 01:34:55', '2010-12-06 01:34:55', '<p style="text-align: center;">[ad#Google Adsense]</p>\n\n<hr />\n\n<div id="rating-block">\n\n[easyreview title="The Stats" cat1title="Coffee Quality" cat1rating="2.5" cat1detail="Utilitarian coffee perfect for those all-nighters." cat2title="Atmosphere" cat2rating="3" cat2detail="Couches, bar and tables abound; lots of windows."]\n\n<table id="info">\n<tr>\n<td class="title">Features <a href="http://localhost/coffeebot/?page_id=195" title="key">(Key)</a></td>\n<td><span class="wifi">WiFi</span><span class="food">Food</span><span class="free-parking">Free parking</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="address">3013 W. 104th Ave. Ste. 700, Westminster, CO 80031</td>\n<td class="phone">(303) 465-0605</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="website"><a href="http://www.rmforzacoffee.com" title="Forza Coffee">Website</a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n\nBot1 had just completed a lecture at CU on the intricacies of wiring a common household goldfish, and like he is after every lecture, found his system needing a certain caffeine boost. We found ourselves at Folsom St. Coffee Co. This is a college joint through and through, and the day we visited it was its usual self: packed, hip...and green. According to their website, Folsom St. Coffee is “Boulder''s only true eco-friendly coffeehouse. Folsom St. Coffee Co. was awarded the Eco-Cycle award for ''Zero Waste or Darn Near'' as well as the "Waste Reduction" award from the Center For Resource Conservation.” I believe it, because when Bot1 tried to throw away his trash, his waste eliminating algorithm caused his CPU to overheat just trying to sort out which tub to throw what in. \n\nBack to the coffee. As has become customary, a double espresso was ordered and Bot1 left to talk up a couple students who were sitting outside. The espresso presented to me had a deceivingly beautiful thick crema that held fast when I spooned some sugar on top. That was a good sign. The flavor, however, was a disappointment. Oddly enough I felt like I was drinking a lime. Of course there were most of the typical espresso qualities, but the acidity was shocking! I''d like to attribute this to the extraction of the shot, but I watched it pour and everything was on the up and up. The flavor evened out when it was in an Americano, but overall I wasn''t too impressed with the flavor.\n\nLike many coffee shops, however, the experience doesn''t always center around the coffee, and ultimately Folsom St. Coffee delivered in other areas. The atmosphere was welcoming, cozy and was the sort of place in which I felt I could get motivated to finally write my 20 page single-spaced essay on the relationship between Pyongyang and Beijing. The muddled and haphazard decor actually cemented the cozy feeling, and that constant murmur of a packed coffee house was ideal for working, meeting friends, or simply sipping a cup of coffee. Complete with poetry, open mic nights and live music acts, this place is hopping a good part of every day, and the sort of place young hipsters like to frequent. \n\nOverall this coffee shop is very enjoyable, and despite being turned down three whole times, Bot1 vowed it wouldn''t keep him down and will definitely return. While the coffee didn''t bowl me over, if you keep it to lattes, Americanos, and brews you won''t be disappointed.  ', 'Folsom St. Coffee Company', 'Bot1 had just completed a lecture at CU on the intricacies of wiring a common household goldfish, and like he is after every lecture, found his system needing a certain caffeine boost. We found ourselves at Folsom St. Coffee Co. ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '316-revision-2', '', '', '2010-12-06 01:34:55', '2010-12-06 01:34:55', '', 316, 'http://coffeebot.co/?p=318', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
