(360, 1, '2010-12-13 18:04:47', '2010-12-13 18:04:47', '<script src="http://connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js#xfbml=1"></script><fb:like show_faces="true" width="450"></fb:like>\r\n<div id="rating-block">\r\n\r\n[easyreview title="The Stats" cat1title="Coffee Quality" cat1rating="4" cat1detail="Killer, well-crafted coffee" cat2title="Atmosphere" cat2rating="3.5" cat2detail="Vibrant and unassuming"]\r\n<table id="info">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="title">Features <a title="key" href="http://localhost/coffeebot/?page_id=195">(Key)</a></td>\r\n<td><span class="food">Food</span><span class="free-parking">free parking</span><span class="wifi">WiFi</span><span class="manual">manual</span><span class="atm">ATM</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="address">2116 Pearl Street, Boulder, CO 80302 </td>\r\n<td class="phone">(303) 247-0124 </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<span class="first-words">“Espressoria” is in the name, why <em>wouldn''t</em> you go there?</span> I discovered this place while trying to go to another coffee shop that was completely packed. Bot1 has no patience for traffic or mobs of people, and when confronted with such situations, his programmed reaction is to drive 30 mph over the speed limit in one direction-stopping for no one. That''s even more dangerous considering the amount of college students and left-over hippies riding around on bicycles in this town. Had he not erupted in such acutely emulated anger, we would never have stumbled across Jet''s Espressoria—quaintly situated slightly off the beaten path in Boulder, Colorado.\r\n\r\n<span class="first-words">The Coffee.</span> An Americano was ordered, and it was presented to me in a mug and with a beautiful golden crema. As I sipped it, my mouth was filled with a wonderful rich, dense, and full-bodied flavor. It was exactly what I needed after riding in a Subaru with a crazed robot. The flavor held, and over the course of my stay the taste never turned extremely acidic, like some coffees tend to do as they cool. This was the work of a fine roast, great espresso skills, and a wonderful espresso machine. Based on a tweet from back in July, they serve Box Car Espresso, Novo Espresso, and Boulder Organic Espresso. For any of you who have read my other posts, you know you usually have me at “Novo”. Judging from the extremely steady stream of customers, they all agreed with the quality as well. \r\n\r\n<span class="first-words">The Atmosphere.</span> This place has a very local, neighborhood, some might say “indie” feel. I interpreted a loose 50''s vibe underscored by photographs of abandoned Route 66-style motels and gas stations, retro-looking tables and chairs and swirling ceiling fans. On the face of it, I personally am not a fan of this kind of look for a coffee shop, but I found myself quite comfortable and Bot1 felt he was among kin, being that most of his metal body work originated from the 50''s. It also had the dinge (which I''m beginning to think is a word I made up) factor I love so much: sketchy paint jobs, cluttered bar and counter, uneven tables and hand-written signs. It was also filled with the bicycle riding naturalists, designers, and college students that Bot1 nearly annihilated on the way over. In short, a great mix of people.\r\n\r\nJet''s Espressoria also bills itself as a bakery and their presentation of fine items was not lacking. Because of their $5 minimum for credit card use, I ordered a blueberry muffin as well. When I do these reviews I''m well aware that I am merely taking a snapshot of an overall experience and I allow quite a bit for less-than-great food, drink, or atmosphere, but this blueberry muffin was, well, not great. That said, I noticed most people going for their assortment of quiches and breakfast burritos which all looked wonderful, and next time I visit I will be digging in to one of these for sure. \r\n\r\n<span class="first-words">The End.</span> Overall this place was a killer find. The coffee quality is way up there and I am very willing to overlook the muffin disappointment in light of the fine coffee and atmosphere. The employees (owners?) were very friendly and seemed genuinely focused on providing an outstanding product. Bring cash or buy lots of stuff since they have a $5 charge minimum, and try it! <span class="end-icon">END</span>\r\n[mappress mapid="7"]\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">[ad#Google Adsense Post Ad]</p>\r\n<hr />', 'Jet''s Espressoria', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '333-revision-10', '', '', '2010-12-13 18:04:47', '2010-12-13 18:04:47', '', 333, 'http://coffeebot.co/uncategorized/333-revision-10/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
