 Hip below-ground art adorned the brick/plaster walls when I first visited, and the room was quite bright thanks to a fairly large red-pained window in the front. I had a bit of trouble finding an outlet for my laptop and finally found one stuck around behind a couch, but I noticed plenty of people on their Macs not bothered by this lack who apparently have risen above the need for a plug. Who needs an outlet, though? This is the sort of place you go to sip your velvety microfoam and discuss bands that don''t exist yet, not necessarily type up your doctoral thesis. There is a tiny bar that you can belly up to and watch the Baristas fashion their creations, and overall, considering the square footage, there is a good amount of seating for the size.\n\nFinally, a few points to note: First, you don''t go there if you are in a rush. It''s obvious the owner is more interested in the beverage quality than in the fact you forgot to set your alarm, spent too much time watching The Kardashians reruns and are now running late for work. Every drink is made one-at-a time which maximizes quality but not speediness. In fact, if you are ordering a latte or cappuccino, each will include some sort of latte design, even if you are slapping a lid on it. Second, Crema''s muffins are insanely good and as a bonus they don''t have the paper wrapper around the bottom so you don''t have to peel it off. Let me tell you, this is reason enough to go there! Finally, they have a great selection of fine teas, but that review is up to TeaBot, not me, and TeaBot doesn''t even exist...yet.\n\n<span class="first-words">The End</span> In conclusion: go there. No excuses, just go. You won''t regret it. \n[mappress mapid="10"]\n<hr />\n<p style="text-align: center">[ad#Google Adsense Post Ad]</p>', 'Crema', '<a href="http://coffeebot.co/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/crema-5-star.jpg"><img src="http://coffeebot.co/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/crema-5-star.jpg" alt="" title="crema-5-star" width="528" height="200" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-438" /></a>\nWhen Bot1 and I discovered an entire coffee shop named after this beauty, it was a no-brainer, or in Bot1''s case, and no-CPUer that we check it out. Everything this shop does, it does well. The website, branding, interior design and ultimately, the beverage are nothing of stellar. Bot1 is programmed to respond to excellence by demanding we go back again, and again, and again since it triggers an infinite loop. Right off the bat, I''d recommend you do the same. ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '407-revision-23', '', '', '2011-01-05 17:33:14', '2011-01-05 17:33:14', '', 407, 'http://coffeebot.co/uncategorized/407-revision-23/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
