(473, 1, '2011-01-09 16:18:14', '2011-01-09 16:18:14', 'I recently discovered Google''s Ngram Viewer and found it really fascinating. Of course, after punching in all the usual suspects: war, peace; male, female; Coke, Pepsi; I punched in coffee and tea. The graph acted a little like I thought it might with tea being fairly dominant for most of history. Both examples rise with the spread of literature and books for the people, but I noticed the rise and fall of mentions that seem to coincide with fairly big historical events. Anyone remember the Boston Tea Party? I am curious then, what other big coffee and tea historical events might be reflected on the graph? For those of you who are A) more knowleageable of history than I am and B) more knowleageable of coffee than I am, I''d love to read what you think. And hop over to Google''s Ngram site, it''s a lot of fun!', 'Coffee & Tea, War & Peace', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '471-revision', '', '', '2011-01-09 16:18:14', '2011-01-09 16:18:14', '', 471, 'http://coffeebot.co/coffee-shop-reviews/471-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
